I fell in love with Pam all over again after watching her Netflix documentary and am about to read her new book, written entirely in her own words. I’m amazed and inspired by Pamela’s courage and her dogged persistence in the pursuit of love and happiness; by the incredible love she has for her boys who love her dearly; by her courageous resilience in the face of life long trauma, choosing love and happiness over fear and despair; and mostly by her big, kind, honest small town Canadian heart❤️ Pamela Anderson shows us, women in our 50’s, that anything is yet possible, and I applaud her bravery for doing so❤️I choose love❤️
.
#pamelaanderson #withlove #canadiangirl #books #bookworm #raedunn

Each morning this week I’ve looked forward to my one hour on the treadmill, not because I love excercise but because I get to listen to Paulina Porizkova’s memoir #nofilter. I’m inspired by the wisdom and courage of the women of my generation. Paulina was also a 1968 refugee from Czechoslovakia so her story resonates with me on a personal level. 
.
#book #memoir #bookworm #paulinaporizkova

Sticky humid days are for reading on my love seat, fan aimed optimally to blow cooled air in my direction. I just finished #badcree by Canadian indigenous writer #JessicaJohns and loved it. It’s a slow burn weaving indigenous trauma with mythology…creepy yet somehow comforting within the bonds of family life. Two thumbs up, give it a read!
.
#booklover  #readthis #bookworm

On July 10th I completed my 57th spin around the sun, where does the time go. This evening I’m in a contemplative mood and also very tired so I’m reclining on my love seat admiring my art collection; each painting has a personal connection that gives me comfort. 7 years ago when I was turning 50 and thought that was a big deal, I commissioned this piece by @sarah_joncas ,  a local talented artist with mad skills. I asked her to paint in one of my rings, swipe to see…and now back to my contemplations…

Hi y’all, it’s been a while! I haven’t been online much these days, too much going on personally. But I have kept up my running and wanted to share a bit of what I’ve learned. I’ve forced myself to slow down (no one cares if you’re a crap runner really!), shaken off the chains of pressure I seem to put on myself no matter the task. Ive deconstructed my running and started from scratch, focusing on form and an easy pace. I’ve been listening to podcasts from @theplantedrunner and follow on IG one of her guests @coachdex_757 . I highly recommend both to anyone starting out or resuming after a long break! I’ve decreased intensity, increased cadence, focused on my foot landing beneath my hips, added a bit of strength training and reduced my running days from 5 to 4, just to name a few changes. Also found a great metronome app (RunTempo) that plays in the background with my music, marking my cadence at 180. Hope this helps someone who is struggling like I was after a 20 year break.
.
#run #runningforjoy5k

Finally I’ve had some time to decompress and get over a bad chest cold; just finished reading #flowersofthekillermoon , wanting to get the most out of watching the movie at some point. It’s not literature so don’t expect to be entertained. What it is, is a meticulously researched  detailed body of work (spanning decades of interviews, FBI reports and much more) that illuminates the depravity and injustice suffered by the Osage at the hands of an insidiously greedy and corrupt system during the dying days of the Wild West and naissance of the 20th Century and Hoover’s FBI. What made it especially chilling was the extent and proliferation of the murderous  schemes, allowing no recourse or escape for those targeted. I’m looking forward to the movie too although I’ve heard the violence is more graphic than needs be. Anyway, it’s one of those books everyone should read IMHO.
.
#booksyoushouldread
